answersResultList.title: Your relationships
answersResultList.resultContent: People matter to you, whether you're intimately involved or barely know them. You go out of your way to engage them, sharing their joy, feeling their pain, or maybe getting a phone number. If this interferes with other responsibilities, so be it. And if asked to evaluate your wealth or count your blessings, you'd start with a list of names.

answersResultList.title: Your health
answersResultList.resultContent: You understand the value of moderation. You're not afraid to set clear limits, because you know that others often expect more than you can reasonably deliver. In your ideal world, you'd maintain a healthy work-play-life balance. That's a worthy goal, but it sets you up for discomfort when people or circumstances fail to harmonize with your balanced vision.
